  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nCut Reeds\nFood Info\n4.7\n1\n0\nRoughage\n(non-survivor food)\nObject Info\n15 sec.\nCan be Burned\n40\nSource\nDropped by\n,\nCrafting\nDescription\nTubular.\nx4\nFilters\nTier\nMiscellaneous\n\"cutreeds\"\n“Cut reeds, ready for crafting and hobbying.”\n–Wilson\n“Cut reeds, ready for burning. Or maybe crafting.”\n–Willow\n“I made a clump of reeds.”\n–Wolfgang\n“I like to cut things up.”\n–Wendy\n“HOLLOW PLANT MATTER”\n–WX-78\n“Some rush cuttings.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“Want to hear my loon call?”\n–Woodie\n“I think I could build something useful from this.”\n–Maxwell\n“Pliable yet tough. Very useful. Very useful indeed.”\n–Wagstaff\n“I cleaned all the bugs öut! Then I ate them.”\n–Wigfrid\n“Reeds, web, what's the difference.”\n–Webber\n“It was hard work cutting those. Nap time!”\n–Walani\n“Smells like greenery.”\n–Warly\n“But Woodlegs can't reed.”\n–Woodlegs\n“'TIS REEDS”\n–Wilba\n“Hair cut”\n–Wormwood\n“Only useful in twos or threes. Or fours or fives.”\n–Wheeler\n“Doesn't hold a candle to steel pipe.”\n–Winona\n“One swift yank was all it took.”\n–Wortox\n“Swamp full of useful things, florp.”\n–Wurt\n“Ms. Wickerbottom might need some more... reed-ing material.”\n–Walter\n“I'll put it in my pocket and use it for something later.”\n–Wanda\nCut Reeds are an item obtained by harvesting Reeds that grow in Swamps. Reeds can be refined into Papyrus and are a crafting ingredient for a Blow Dart, Sleep Dart, Fire Dart and Pan Flute. Reeds grow back after 3 days from being picked, but they will not grow in Winter.\nThere is an alternative method of obtaining Cut Reeds: by destroying Tumbleweeds. There is a 1% chance of it dropping from the 3 possible drops. Also, a friendly Catcoon can gift the player Cut Reeds.\nReeds can also be harvested from the Rocky Beach biome on the Lunar Island.\nMonkeytails are another source of Cut Reeds that can be transplanted near one's base for easy harvesting.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×4\n×5\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×5\n×2\n×4\n×4\n×15\n×3\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×3\n×3\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nOriginal HD icon from Bonus Materials from CD Don't Starve.\nResourcesFood\nView or edit this template\nResources\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/behavior/function/tags of these items\nPlants\nNatural non-living materials\nMobs Parts\nSkins\nFeathers\nBones and horns\nGems\nShadow Resources\nLunar Resources\nCraftable Resources\nNon-natural materials\nTrinkets\nLost Relics\nTransmission Items\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
